562
00:42:02,936 --> 00:42:05,769
- I'd just like to go home.
- Well, you're free to go.

563
00:42:06,006 --> 00:42:10,636
- You sure were cool under fire, ma'am.
- I'll faint at home. Thanks.

564
00:42:11,611 --> 00:42:13,238
Sorry.

565
00:42:13,446 --> 00:42:17,405
Mr. Harper? How much did you
tell them that you lost?

566
00:42:17,651 --> 00:42:19,118
$ 1000. What do you mean?

567
00:42:19,352 --> 00:42:20,819
You couldn't tell them $2000?

568
00:42:20,987 --> 00:42:25,151
Insurance would have paid. I would have
split the extra grand with you. Schmuck.

569
00:42:31,765 --> 00:42:34,290
- Hi, Mom. Hi, Dad.
- Billy, are you going outside?

570
00:42:34,467 --> 00:42:35,456
Yeah.

571
00:42:35,635 --> 00:42:37,500
- Hi, Bill.
- Hi.

572
00:42:42,475 --> 00:42:44,409
Are you feeling all right?

573
00:42:45,645 --> 00:42:47,772
Come in and close the door.

574
00:42:49,649 --> 00:42:51,139
Lock it.

575
00:42:54,287 --> 00:42:58,815
They dropped it, I fell on it, and while the
police chased them I put it in my bag.

576
00:42:59,192 --> 00:43:00,784
Oh, my God!

577
00:43:01,061 --> 00:43:03,586
I don't know what happened to me.
I just did it.

578
00:43:03,763 --> 00:43:07,255
- There's 2000 dollars here.
- I can't believe I did it.

579
00:43:07,434 --> 00:43:10,801
- Neither can I.
- It's not funny. I've committed a crime.

580
00:43:10,970 --> 00:43:12,801
And done a hell of a job at it.

581
00:43:15,175 --> 00:43:16,608
Why didn't I give it back?

582
00:43:16,776 --> 00:43:19,176
It never occurred
to me to give it back.

583
00:43:19,345 --> 00:43:22,371
- You're sensational.
- I can't believe it. Stop it, Dick.

584
00:43:22,749 --> 00:43:25,445
Would you turn on the faucet?

585
00:43:25,852 --> 00:43:28,946
- I'm going to give it back.
- To who, the robbers?

586
00:43:29,589 --> 00:43:31,955
The money belongs to the loan...

587
00:43:32,992 --> 00:43:35,552
- They have insurance, don't they?
- Exactly.

588
00:43:35,762 --> 00:43:37,923
Suppose they catch those guys.
They saw me.

589
00:43:38,098 --> 00:43:42,194
They'll never catch them. Even if they
finger you, who's going to believe them?

590
00:43:42,368 --> 00:43:45,667
The cops won't believe them.
They'll think they spent it all.

591
00:43:45,839 --> 00:43:48,000
I can't believe we're talking like this.

592
00:43:48,441 --> 00:43:51,342
Dick. We've always done
things the straight way.

593
00:43:51,511 --> 00:43:55,743
Yeah, well, I'm tired of
belonging to a minority group.

594
00:43:57,217 --> 00:43:59,014
Okay.

595
00:43:59,252 --> 00:44:02,153
- Okay, I'm going to keep it.
- Good.

596
00:44:02,622 --> 00:44:06,319
- I'm going to keep it.
- That's still good.

597
00:44:07,761 --> 00:44:11,458
Hey. Do you think it would be awful
if we had a little celebration?

598
00:44:11,798 --> 00:44:15,290
- Something besides Hamburger Helper?
- A little red wine.

599
00:44:15,468 --> 00:44:19,336
How about a little champagne?

600
00:44:21,007 --> 00:44:24,443
- Love you.
- I love you.

601
00:44:29,315 --> 00:44:32,512
Got the lights. We got our lights back.

602
00:44:33,019 --> 00:44:34,782
I propose a toast.

603
00:44:34,954 --> 00:44:37,388
- Down with candles.
- Down with imitation mayonnaise.

604
00:44:37,557 --> 00:44:40,321
- Down with Hamburger Helper.
- Up the Harpers.

605
00:44:41,027 --> 00:44:42,824
Here's looking at you, Spot.

606
00:44:43,296 --> 00:44:44,285
Wow.

607
00:44:44,464 --> 00:44:46,830
- You can have some.
- Will you get that, honey?

608
00:44:47,033 --> 00:44:48,830
- Sure.
- Spotty, old boy.

609
00:44:50,003 --> 00:44:53,530
- Yes?
- Is this the residence of Richard Harper?

610
00:44:59,012 --> 00:45:00,502
Yes, I'm Mrs. Harper.

611
00:45:01,114 --> 00:45:03,742
You've applied for the
food stamp program?

612
00:45:04,751 --> 00:45:05,775
That's right.

613
00:45:05,952 --> 00:45:09,683
My name is Johnson. I'm the
income maintenance technician.

614
00:45:10,290 --> 00:45:11,279
The what?

615
00:45:11,457 --> 00:45:13,857
I've come for the inspection.

616
00:45:16,329 --> 00:45:19,196
- Tonight?
- Want to see my credentials, lady?

617
00:45:19,699 --> 00:45:22,429
No. No.

618
00:45:23,837 --> 00:45:25,134
Please come in.

619
00:45:35,415 --> 00:45:39,613
Darling, this is Mr. Johnson.
The income maintenance mechanic.

620
00:45:39,786 --> 00:45:41,117
Technician.

621
00:45:41,487 --> 00:45:44,513
The food stamps fellow.

622
00:45:54,801 --> 00:45:58,897
- Have you eaten, Mr. Johnson?
- Yes, I had a Big Mac and a small fries.

623
00:46:00,840 --> 00:46:03,434
- You don't understand...
- Don't I?

624
00:46:05,378 --> 00:46:08,745
- Would you like some champagne?
- And I also had a Coke.

625
00:46:11,551 --> 00:46:15,783
Truth is, we ripped off a loan company,
and this is the last of our proceeds.

626
00:46:16,389 --> 00:46:18,482
I see, yes.

627
00:46:19,492 --> 00:46:22,359
You want to see if we have
any cooking facilities, right?

628
00:46:23,563 --> 00:46:25,497
Yes. Yes, that's the first thing.

629
00:46:26,633 --> 00:46:28,225
This way.

630
00:46:33,907 --> 00:46:36,171
You don't have any assets
other than what's here?

631
00:46:36,509 --> 00:46:37,635
That's it.

632
00:46:39,045 --> 00:46:41,536
You sure messed up real good.

633
00:46:42,882 --> 00:46:43,974
We sure did.

634
00:46:44,150 --> 00:46:47,176
Never mind the editorials,
are we eligible or not?

635
00:46:48,855 --> 00:46:52,222
- According to the rules, you're eligible.
- Thank you.

636
00:46:52,525 --> 00:46:56,325
Don't thank me. It's people like you
who give this program a bad name.

637
00:46:56,496 --> 00:46:58,521
Screw it up for others who need it.

638
00:46:58,965 --> 00:47:00,330
I don't think that's fair.

639
00:47:00,500 --> 00:47:04,231
Jane, the old rich are
always sticking it to the new rich.

640
00:47:04,404 --> 00:47:06,929
The old poor have to stick
it to the nouveau poor.

641
00:47:07,106 --> 00:47:10,166
- We, in this case, are the nouveau poor.
- We really need it.

642
00:47:10,343 --> 00:47:13,107
No one in this house or in
this neighborhood needs it.

643
00:47:13,279 --> 00:47:17,511
Really? You think we should sell
this house and move to a slum.

644
00:47:17,684 --> 00:47:19,549
We should sell before the bank does.

645
00:47:19,719 --> 00:47:22,085
- Which is next week.
- You can just forget it.

646
00:47:22,255 --> 00:47:24,246
- We're keeping this house.
- How?

647
00:47:24,424 --> 00:47:26,449
- We'll make the payments!
- With what?

648
00:47:26,859 --> 00:47:30,192
You have accepted our current
problems as permanent. They are not.

649
00:47:30,363 --> 00:47:31,830
This is only temporary.

650
00:47:31,998 --> 00:47:33,932
You haven't told me how we'll
make the payments!

651
00:47:34,200 --> 00:47:37,226
The middle class is the
backbone of this country.

652
00:47:37,403 --> 00:47:40,804
We've got to survive. If we go
under, the whole country can.

653
00:47:40,974 --> 00:47:44,341
And in these, our bicentennial
years, my contribution...

654
00:47:44,510 --> 00:47:47,775
...isn't the destruction of
the American middle class!

655
00:47:47,947 --> 00:47:51,542
I don't know what you're...
Billy, entertain our guest, please.

656
00:47:51,851 --> 00:47:55,343
- We have nothing to worry about?
- Right. Nothing to worry about.

657
00:47:55,521 --> 00:47:58,046
- I'll speak to the bank tomorrow.
- I spoke to them today.

658
00:47:58,224 --> 00:48:00,692
He said, "You are no
longer banking with us...

659
00:48:00,860 --> 00:48:03,920
...we're banking with you."
- Very funny. Leave it to me.

660
00:48:04,097 --> 00:48:05,997
- We'll make the payment.
- With what?

661
00:48:06,165 --> 00:48:07,632
We'll make the payment.

662
00:48:19,779 --> 00:48:21,371
This is a stickup.

663
00:48:22,348 --> 00:48:23,542
Stick them up.

664
00:48:24,951 --> 00:48:26,077
Stick them up.

665
00:48:26,452 --> 00:48:29,353
Stick them up. Stick them up.

666
00:48:34,627 --> 00:48:39,155
This is a stickup! Stick
them up! Stick them up!

667
00:48:40,700 --> 00:48:41,894
Stick them up.

668
00:48:42,235 --> 00:48:43,725
Stick them up.

669
00:48:43,936 --> 00:48:45,494
Are you kidding?

670
00:48:47,240 --> 00:48:48,571
Are you crazy?

671
00:48:48,841 --> 00:48:52,971
Don't come in when I have a gun in my
hand! You'll get your head blown off!

672
00:48:53,212 --> 00:48:57,273
Take that ridiculous thing off your face.
I can't hear a word you're saying.

673
00:48:57,550 --> 00:49:00,280
Never sneak up on a man
holding a gun. You can get killed.

674
00:49:00,453 --> 00:49:02,148
- What are you doing with a gun?
- I'm...

675
00:49:02,321 --> 00:49:04,312
Never mind.
I know what you're gonna do.

676
00:49:04,490 --> 00:49:07,584
Yeah, well, you're right about that.

677
00:49:07,760 --> 00:49:09,785
And give me the keys to the car.

678
00:49:09,962 --> 00:49:13,125
- Hasn't this gone far enough?
- You're not gonna stop me.

679
00:49:13,299 --> 00:49:16,496
I'm gonna get that money.

680
00:49:16,669 --> 00:49:19,331
Is getting arrested gonna help us
get the money?

681
00:49:19,505 --> 00:49:21,496
You don't think I can do it, do you?

682
00:49:21,674 --> 00:49:23,904
I'm a washout. I'm a loser.

683
00:49:24,077 --> 00:49:28,013
Not even capable of holding up
a goddamn grocery store.

684
00:49:28,181 --> 00:49:30,809
Any idiot can hold up a grocery store.

685
00:49:30,983 --> 00:49:33,178
Thank you.

686
00:49:39,559 --> 00:49:42,722
- You're really determined to do this.
- That's right, Jane.

687
00:49:42,895 --> 00:49:44,829
- That what you're gonna wear?
- Yeah.

688
00:49:44,997 --> 00:49:46,988
- What do you think?
- I think you look like...

689
00:49:47,166 --> 00:49:49,361
...the Easter Bunny bandit.
- I had to ask.

690
00:49:49,569 --> 00:49:52,060
You might as well wear a sign
that says, "Arrest me."

691
00:49:52,271 --> 00:49:54,466
Okay, what do you think I should wear?

692
00:49:54,874 --> 00:49:58,002
Why don't you wear something
a little more inconspicuous, like...

693
00:49:58,177 --> 00:49:59,542
...the Batman costume?

694
00:50:13,359 --> 00:50:14,485
How's this?

695
00:50:14,660 --> 00:50:15,786
It's fine.

696
00:50:15,962 --> 00:50:18,453
Okay, baby. I'm off.

697
00:50:18,631 --> 00:50:19,757
- Dick?
- Yeah?

698
00:50:19,932 --> 00:50:22,901
Don't you think we've
forgotten something?

699
00:50:23,069 --> 00:50:25,401
The iron. Right.

700
00:50:35,181 --> 00:50:38,241
Dick, don't you think that gun
is gonna attract attention...

701
00:50:38,417 --> 00:50:42,012
...sticking out of your belt like that?
- I'll wear a jacket. Don't worry.

702
00:50:42,188 --> 00:50:44,713
I have to worry. I was a psych major.

703
00:50:44,891 --> 00:50:47,291
You know what Freud said.
Criminals leave clues.

704
00:50:47,460 --> 00:50:49,485
They have a compulsion to confess.

705
00:50:49,662 --> 00:50:53,291
