- Inspirational sermon, doctor.
- Thank you, thank you.

934
01:10:41,419 --> 01:10:45,321
Yes, particularly the part about
not feeling guilty about prospering.

935
01:10:45,490 --> 01:10:48,550
Well, you see,
that is called "Say 'I am."'

936
01:10:48,727 --> 01:10:53,096
If you want more money, you must get
an expanded idea of yourself.

937
01:10:53,264 --> 01:10:55,994
You must think of yourself
as one who has more money.

938
01:10:56,201 --> 01:10:58,601
We're trying, doctor.

939
01:10:59,204 --> 01:11:03,334
Well, go ahead. Touch it, son.
Don't be afraid. Go on.

940
01:11:04,075 --> 01:11:06,509
Go ahead, dear, touch it.

941
01:11:08,446 --> 01:11:13,679
Go on. That's it, touch it some more.

942
01:11:14,052 --> 01:11:17,283
You see, you must take the limit
off your financial thinking...

943
01:11:17,489 --> 01:11:20,424
...and you will get more money.
Don't worry about how.

944
01:11:20,625 --> 01:11:23,150
- Inspirational.
- Say "I am."

945
01:11:23,361 --> 01:11:25,158
Stick them up.

946
01:11:26,297 --> 01:11:28,822
Did I hear you right, sinner?
You holding me up?

947
01:11:29,033 --> 01:11:32,730
I am. Hands on your head, both of you.

948
01:11:35,340 --> 01:11:37,103
- Move!
- Will you get out of the way?

949
01:11:37,275 --> 01:11:42,235
- God wants you out of the way!
- Guards!

950
01:11:56,895 --> 01:11:59,796
Stop them, for they have sinned!

951
01:12:00,298 --> 01:12:03,495
Would you mind
getting the hell off the car?

952
01:12:04,102 --> 01:12:06,593
<i>Testing. Testing.</i>

953
01:12:10,074 --> 01:12:12,372
Oh, Jesus!

954
01:12:14,913 --> 01:12:17,746
- You all right?
- Yeah, I think so.

955
01:12:24,322 --> 01:12:28,156
<i>Pull over, you sinners!</i>
<i>They are thieves, stop them!</i>

956
01:12:28,326 --> 01:12:31,056
<i>They have stolen all my</i>...
<i>The Lord's money.</i>

957
01:12:31,229 --> 01:12:34,198
- Oh, no!
- God!

958
01:12:34,399 --> 01:12:37,334
<i>If you pull over at the next light,</i>
<i>God will forgive you.</i>

959
01:12:37,535 --> 01:12:39,298
- <i>He is no stool pigeon.</i>
- Oh, my God!

960
01:12:39,471 --> 01:12:42,963
<i>God does not hold a grudge.</i>
<i>Remember, thou shalt not steal.</i>

961
01:12:43,141 --> 01:12:44,870
They're coming closer to us, Dick.

962
01:12:45,076 --> 01:12:49,740
<i>That is the fourth</i>...
<i>That's one of them commandments.</i>

963
01:12:50,782 --> 01:12:53,012
<i>Give me back my</i>
<i>goddamn money, will you?</i>

964
01:12:53,184 --> 01:12:56,347
<i>Step on it. Can't you get more</i>
<i>juice out of this goddamn thing?</i>

965
01:12:56,521 --> 01:13:00,958
<i>Watch out! Jesus Christ!</i>
<i>You almost broke my ass, you fool.</i>

966
01:13:02,427 --> 01:13:03,951
Oh, a cop!

967
01:13:51,376 --> 01:13:53,401
That is my money!

968
01:14:18,536 --> 01:14:20,026
How much we get?

969
01:14:20,204 --> 01:14:23,662
Not very much. It's mostly ones.

970
01:14:23,841 --> 01:14:28,505
Mostly ones?
Hey, where's the other money?

971
01:14:28,680 --> 01:14:30,648
What other money?

972
01:14:30,815 --> 01:14:33,648
All the other money,
that's what other money.

973
01:14:33,818 --> 01:14:36,810
- In the shrubbery.
- In the shrubbery?

974
01:14:36,988 --> 01:14:38,956
In the pool.

975
01:14:40,024 --> 01:14:41,548
In the swimming pool?

976
01:14:41,759 --> 01:14:44,694
It's in the utilities,
it's in the car, in the furniture...

977
01:14:44,862 --> 01:14:50,027
...it's in the mortgage, in the insurance.
It's at the Diners Club.

978
01:15:00,912 --> 01:15:05,246
Well, it's not worth it.
I'm not cut out for blue-collar crime.

979
01:15:05,416 --> 01:15:08,749
I have a white-collar mentality.
I panic in the face of death.

980
01:15:15,059 --> 01:15:17,857
Maybe we should retire.

981
01:15:23,067 --> 01:15:26,559
- Are all our debts paid?
- Yes.

982
01:15:27,205 --> 01:15:32,233
At least we won't starve. We've just been
accepted by the food stamp program.

983
01:15:32,410 --> 01:15:34,275
Hurray.

984
01:15:36,481 --> 01:15:38,210
- Charlie!
- Where?

985
01:15:39,017 --> 01:15:41,679
<i>Mr. Blanchard, I would like you</i>
<i>to tell this committee...</i>

986
01:15:41,886 --> 01:15:46,482
<i>... if you have ever, in your position</i>
<i>as president of Taft, bribed anyone...</i>

987
01:15:46,658 --> 01:15:51,186
<i>... either here or abroad, for the purpose</i>
<i>of consummating a business deal.</i>

988
01:15:51,462 --> 01:15:57,458
<i>Senator, no one at Taft Aerospace,</i>
<i>to the best of my knowledge...</i>

989
01:15:57,635 --> 01:15:59,535
<i>... ever bribed anybody.</i>

990
01:16:01,506 --> 01:16:04,805
<i>Maybe that's why business is so bad.</i>

991
01:16:05,243 --> 01:16:08,804
Look at him. Listen to him shovel it.

992
01:16:08,980 --> 01:16:13,576
There's never been a deal at Taft where
somebody didn't get paid off somewhere.

993
01:16:14,085 --> 01:16:16,952
<i>We have already elicited testimony</i>
<i>from other companies...</i>

994
01:16:17,121 --> 01:16:19,487
<i>... involved in the same</i>
<i>business as yours...</i>

995
01:16:19,657 --> 01:16:24,094
<i>... and they claim that payoffs are an</i>
<i>integral part of carrying on business.</i>

996
01:16:24,529 --> 01:16:27,623
<i>Do you mean to tell me</i>
<i>that you are the exception?</i>

997
01:16:27,832 --> 01:16:30,528
You know, guys walk into his office
and walk out again...

998
01:16:30,702 --> 01:16:34,502
...with $200,000 cash in a briefcase.

999
01:16:34,672 --> 01:16:37,937
- Two hundred thousand dollars?
- Watch him. Watch him bob and weave.

1000
01:16:40,244 --> 01:16:44,704
<i>Senator. Now, we at Taft Aerospace</i>
<i>have always prided ourselves...</i>

1001
01:16:44,882 --> 01:16:47,282
<i>... in truth on what we produce.</i>

1002
01:16:47,485 --> 01:16:51,683
- Charlie does his laundry.
- Any idea where he keeps it?

1003
01:16:51,856 --> 01:16:54,518
Yeah, in the safe in his office.

1004
01:17:00,364 --> 01:17:02,491
Fortunately, there are guards
everywhere...

1005
01:17:02,667 --> 01:17:06,034
...and I don't even have a key to
the executive washroom anymore.

1006
01:17:06,204 --> 01:17:11,141
Unfortunately, we've been invited
to a party at Taft next week.

1007
01:17:14,212 --> 01:17:17,909
Fortunately, we don't know
the first thing about safecracking.

1008
01:17:18,082 --> 01:17:22,143
Unfortunately, we are fast learners.

1009
01:17:23,621 --> 01:17:26,954
- Short retirement.
- Very.

1010
01:17:34,766 --> 01:17:36,461
- I felt it.
- Positive?

1011
01:17:36,634 --> 01:17:39,865
Of course I'm positive, honey.
It's gotta be perfect.

1012
01:17:40,037 --> 01:17:43,302
- I've been practicing for days.
- And you've almost got it. Come on.

1013
01:17:43,474 --> 01:17:45,203
You ready? Okay.

1014
01:17:45,376 --> 01:17:50,712
- Deft. Deft. And deft.
- Okay.

1015
01:17:50,882 --> 01:17:54,841
- You should tell me when I should do it.
- Whenever you're ready.

1016
01:18:26,517 --> 01:18:29,247
Well, it's just like old times.

1017
01:18:29,420 --> 01:18:33,254
- I hope you brought the old equalizer.
- Will you cut it out?

1018
01:18:33,424 --> 01:18:35,722
- Hi, Pete, how are you?
- Who is it?

1019
01:18:35,893 --> 01:18:38,987
Pete Winston. Wife, Betty.
Super Bowl, back operation.

1020
01:18:39,163 --> 01:18:42,064
- Really good to see you. How are you?
- Great. Just great.

1021
01:18:42,233 --> 01:18:43,894
You know my wife, Jane, don't you?

1022
01:18:44,068 --> 01:18:47,663
- I don't know if she'll remember me.
- Winston, how can you say that?

1023
01:18:47,839 --> 01:18:51,275
We met you and Betty at the Super Bowl
last winter. How's your back?

1024
01:18:51,442 --> 01:18:53,569
- How nice of you to remember.
- Is Betty here?

1025
01:18:53,744 --> 01:18:55,871
- She's in the back.
- I'll be glad to see her.

1026
01:18:56,047 --> 01:18:58,515
- She'd love to see you too.
- There you are.

1027
01:18:58,683 --> 01:19:00,207
- Charlie.
- What I want to know is...

1028
01:19:00,384 --> 01:19:03,182
...do I get to kiss your wife,
or do I have to make a scene?

1029
01:19:03,354 --> 01:19:07,017
- Do we know this man?
- Some guy who still works at the plant.

1030
01:19:11,863 --> 01:19:12,852
Hi, Charlie.

1031
01:19:13,030 --> 01:19:15,396
I don't know what a good-looking guy
like Dick sees in you.

1032
01:19:15,566 --> 01:19:17,932
- I do yard work.
- You can do work in my yard anytime.

1033
01:19:18,135 --> 01:19:19,534
- Charlie.
- You wanna dance?

1034
01:19:19,704 --> 01:19:21,672
I'd love to.

1035
01:19:25,109 --> 01:19:26,872
- Very nice.
- What?

1036
01:19:27,044 --> 01:19:30,980
- I said, very nice.
- Perfect.

1037
01:20:57,034 --> 01:20:58,296
Charlie, no!

1038
01:20:58,469 --> 01:21:02,166
No? I won't take "no" for an answer.
I'll be waiting.

1039
01:21:21,959 --> 01:21:24,291
Showoff.

1040
01:21:34,438 --> 01:21:38,374
Come on. Dick, Charlie's gonna
come to his office at 11:00.

1041
01:21:38,542 --> 01:21:39,873
- All right.
- We gotta hurry.

1042
01:21:40,044 --> 01:21:43,844
All right. Will you get out of the way?

1043
01:21:46,917 --> 01:21:49,215
Hey, you! Don't move.

1044
01:21:51,722 --> 01:21:54,213
Take that, you honky putz.

1045
01:22:00,965 --> 01:22:03,092
- Oh, my God!
- What?

1046
01:22:14,912 --> 01:22:17,073
Come on, will you?

1047
01:22:19,917 --> 01:22:21,782
Come on.

1048
01:22:39,136 --> 01:22:40,763
- These are all make-believe.
- Dick.

1049
01:22:40,938 --> 01:22:42,838
What?

1050
01:22:43,007 --> 01:22:44,497
Does he have a closet?

1051
01:22:44,675 --> 01:22:47,439
I read in the book the most
popular place for safes are...

1052
01:22:47,611 --> 01:22:50,580
- He does indeed have a closet.
- Okay.

1053
01:22:57,521 --> 01:22:59,716
I love you, Jane.

1054
01:23:00,858 --> 01:23:06,319
- Thanks.
- Mosler, model number 1874.

1055
01:23:07,698 --> 01:23:11,759
Mosler. Okay.

1056
01:23:13,971 --> 01:23:18,169
There. Right there is where
you have to drill.

1057
01:23:32,556 --> 01:23:37,858
Dick, it's okay. You can hardly hear
the drilling out here.

1058
01:23:47,738 --> 01:23:49,865
Dick, somebody's coming.

1059
01:23:57,515 --> 01:23:59,710
In the closet.

1060
01:24:09,593 --> 01:24:13,620
- Is it the guard?
- I don't know. I couldn't see.

1061
01:24:22,373 --> 01:24:26,070
It can't be Charlie. It's only 10:15.

1062
01:24:26,243 --> 01:24:28,177
Let me look.

1063
01:24:33,417 --> 01:24:37,114
I can't see anything.
Maybe he won't look in here.

1064
01:24:37,288 --> 01:24:39,483
- Suppose he does?
- Screw him.

1065
01:24:39,657 --> 01:24:42,251
I most certainly will not.

1066
01:24:55,906 --> 01:24:58,739
- That wasn't Charlie.
- Really.

1067
01:25:18,462 --> 01:25:20,555
Come on in.

1068
01:25:31,242 --> 01:25:34,769
Hey, everybody, come on in.

1069
01:25:37,314 --> 01:25:40,545
Hey, my man, what's happening?

1070
01:25:58,502 --> 01:26:02,563
Jane! They're never going to hear the
drill over this. I'm going back to work.

1071
01:26:02,740 --> 01:26:05,004
If somebody's coming, just let me know.

1072
01:26:38,976 --> 01:26:41,706
Jane, it's your turn.

1073
01:27:29,059 --> 01:27:32,722
- It's all the money in the world.
- It gives me goose flesh.

1074
01:27:33,564 --> 01:27:35,964
Oh, my God.

1075
01:27:58,055 --> 01:28:01,957
- Floor show. Floor show.
- Go on.

1076
01:28:02,126 --> 01:28:04,492
Get y'all gone. We talking business.

1077
01:28:06,063 --> 01:28:10,056
- I need more.
- Okay, just a second. Okay, okay.

1078
01:28:10,234 --> 01:28:12,202
It feels so good.

1079
01:28:13,170 --> 01:28:15,934
That's what I've been looking for.
Thank you very much.

1080
01:28:16,106 --> 01:28:19,872
Guys, have a good time,
enjoy yourselves. This is a party.

1081
01:28:28,051 --> 01:28:33,819
Okay. Get the elevator. Around through
the boardroom and to the left.

1082
01:28:41,532 --> 01:28:43,591
Gotcha!

1083
01:28:46,036 --> 01:28:50,666
- Dick followed me up here.
- Hey, Charlie.

1084
01:28:50,874 --> 01:28:53,069
Dick, boy. Hi.

1085
01:28:56,313 --> 01:29:01,216
- Going down?
- Down, yes. Lobby, please.

1086
01:29:01,385 --> 01:29:04,582
Funny, we're going to the lobby too.

1087
01:29:09,092 --> 01:29:12,926
Well, I guess we can all ride together.

1088
01:29:19,269 --> 01:29:21,533
I don't feel very well.
I think we should go.

1089
01:29:21,705 --> 01:29:24,139
Not until you have one
little drink with Charlie.

1090
01:29:24,308 --> 01:29:27,971
- No, Charlie, I really think...
- Here, let me take your purse.

1091
01:29:29,279 --> 01:29:31,543
One little nightcap.

1092
01:29:48,899 --> 01:29:51,629
Nobility. Pride.

1093
01:29:51,802 --> 01:29:55,465
A sense of feeling that
your life amounts to something.

1094
01:29:55,639 --> 01:29:58,802
That's what we lost when
we lost the space program.

1095
01:29:58,976 --> 01:30:01,035
- Sir?
- Nobil... Nobil...

1096
01:30:01,211 --> 01:30:02,940
- What?
- May I have a word with you?

1097
01:30:03,113 --> 01:30:04,671
- Right now?
- Yes, sir.

1098
01:30:04,848 --> 01:30:08,750
Hey, listen. Don't go away.
I'll be right back.

1099
01:30:09,353 --> 01:30:10,843
Let's go.

1100
01:30:11,021 --> 01:30:13,216
Where? Where are we going?

1101
01:30:21,164 --> 01:30:24,793
- We were just gonna walk right out.
- We were. We were.

1102
01:30:27,004 --> 01:30:30,235
There's nothing to worry about.
Charlie wouldn't call the cops.

1103
01:30:30,407 --> 01:30:33,103
This money doesn't exist.
Don't you understand?

1104
01:30:33,277 --> 01:30:36,610
What about all these security guards?
Do they exist or don't they?

1105
01:30:41,518 --> 01:30:46,285
Wait a minute.
Dick, we gotta call the cops.

1106
01:30:46,456 --> 01:30:48,856
- Are you crazy?
- No, no, I'm not kidding.

1107
01:30:49,026 --> 01:30:51,494
Charlie's never gonna admit
there's a slush fund.

1108
01:30:51,662 --> 01:30:55,564
If he sees cops all around, he's gonna
make sure we get out of here safely.

1109
01:30:55,732 --> 01:30:58,360
With the money.

1110
01:30:59,202 --> 01:31:02,262
You're very smart, Jane.

1111
01:31:04,541 --> 01:31:07,135
- Have you got a dime?
- A dime?

1112
01:31:07,311 --> 01:31:09,472
- Yeah.
- No. You?

1113
01:31:13,550 --> 01:31:17,850
Find someone with change of
1000 dollars, for chrissake.

1114
01:31:29,099 --> 01:31:32,432
- Jane feeling better?
- Oh, yeah. Yeah, sure.

1115
01:31:32,603 --> 01:31:35,333
Dick, there's something
I've been meaning to ask you.

1116
01:31:35,505 --> 01:31:37,268
Shoot.

1117
01:31:37,441 --> 01:31:40,672
What's in the bag?
Your makeup?

1118
01:31:42,546 --> 01:31:44,741
Charlie, Charlie.

1119
01:31:49,019 --> 01:31:50,816
- Charlie, can I level with you?
- Sure.

1120
01:31:50,988 --> 01:31:54,856
- Well, I mean really level with you.
- You can tell me anything.

1121
01:31:55,025 --> 01:31:59,621
We just cleaned out your safe.
Every last buck.

1122
01:32:02,099 --> 01:32:04,499
- Did you now?
- Yeah.

1123
01:32:04,668 --> 01:32:09,002
I'm sorry. I shouldn't have said it
straight-out like that.

1124
01:32:09,172 --> 01:32:13,040
But I'm just sick of all the bullshit,
you know what I mean?

1125
01:32:13,210 --> 01:32:15,110
How do you propose
to get out of here?

1126
01:32:15,278 --> 01:32:18,338
- With your help, Charlie.
- My help?

1127
01:32:18,515 --> 01:32:21,177
Do you see that big dude over there?

1128
01:32:21,385 --> 01:32:25,845
He can shoot the eye out
of a hummingbird at 50 paces.

1129
01:32:27,591 --> 01:32:31,391
Charlie, we just called the cops.

1130
01:32:43,407 --> 01:32:46,570
- We're gonna give ourselves up.
- This is no joke, friends.

1131
01:32:46,777 --> 01:32:50,577
- We're gonna make a clean breast of it.
- Don't be stupid.

1132
01:32:50,747 --> 01:32:54,979
You keep your mouth shut,
and I'll see that you get out of here.

1133
01:32:55,152 --> 01:32:56,210
With the money?

1134
01:33:00,924 --> 01:33:03,222
You son of a bitch.

1135
01:33:07,264 --> 01:33:12,861
Officers, I'm Charles Blanchard.
I'm the president of Taft Aerospace.

1136
01:33:13,036 --> 01:33:14,469
Maybe I can be of help.

1137
01:33:15,806 --> 01:33:19,503
Dear, you've just seen a demonstration
of what we in the corporate world...

1138
01:33:19,676 --> 01:33:23,077
...refer to as
"hardballing it with the big guys."

1139
01:33:23,246 --> 01:33:26,010
I enjoyed it thoroughly.

1140
01:33:26,183 --> 01:33:29,346
Would you be embarrassed
if I kissed you in a public place?

1141
01:33:29,519 --> 01:33:32,283
I'd be embarrassed if you kissed me
in a private place...

1142
01:33:32,456 --> 01:33:34,083
...with all these people around.

1143
01:33:35,759 --> 01:33:39,217
I'm afraid, officer, that you've been
a victim of a drunken prankster...

1144
01:33:39,396 --> 01:33:44,766
...but if you'd excuse me for one minute,
this young lady isn't feeling very well.

1145
01:33:44,935 --> 01:33:45,924
I'm sorry.

1146
01:33:46,103 --> 01:33:49,561
If I could get these two out of here,
I'd feel a lot better. Run along.

1147
01:33:49,740 --> 01:33:53,938
Now we can talk about that
ridiculous story about my safe.

1148
01:33:54,311 --> 01:33:57,940
- Jane...
- Come along, Jane. Come along.